{"findings":[{"id":"F-001","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Staked balance can be reused as LP principal while staking units remain active","locations":["superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidLocker.sol:354","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidLocker.sol:363","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidLocker.sol:420","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidLocker.sol:436","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidLocker.sol:565","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidLocker.sol:688"],"claim":"Staking only increases `_stakedBalance` and staker pool units, while `provideLiquidity()` does not check `getAvailableBalance()` before approving and minting with `supAmount`. The Uniswap mint can therefore consume FLUID that is still counted as staked, and `_createPosition()` then grants LP units without reducing staker units.","impact":"A locker owner can use the same FLUID principal to receive both staker and LP tax/reward distributions, diluting honest stakers and liquidity providers and extracting excess emissions. After the rehypothecation, `getAvailableBalance()` can also underflow until the locker receives enough FLUID again because `_stakedBalance` exceeds the actual token balance.","paths":["Lock X FLUID into the locker.","Call `stake(X)`, which increases `_stakedBalance` and updates staker units.","Call `provideLiquidity()` with `supAmount` close to X; the Uniswap position manager pulls the same FLUID from the locker even though it is still counted as staked.","The locker keeps staker units and also receives LP units based on the new liquidity position."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Anyone can stop program funding during the early-end window","locations":["superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidEPProgramManager.sol:339","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidEPProgramManager.sol:349","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidEPProgramManager.sol:353","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidEPProgramManager.sol:365","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidEPProgramManager.sol:380"],"claim":"`stopFunding()` is external and has no owner or program-admin restriction. Any account can call it once `block.timestamp >= endDate - EARLY_PROGRAM_END`, causing the manager to delete program details, stop the flow, and distribute the remaining early-end compensation using the current pool units.","impact":"An attacker or advantaged participant can front-run late unit updates in the final three days and force the remaining compensation to be distributed at a favorable snapshot, distorting the final reward allocation and disrupting program operations.","paths":["Wait until a funded program reaches `endDate - 3 days`.","Before expected admin or signer-driven unit updates execute, call `stopFunding(programId)` from any address.","The manager stops the flow and performs the compensation distribution using the pre-update units."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Unit-update signatures are replayable across deployments and chains","locations":["superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/EPProgramManager.sol:164","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/EPProgramManager.sol:168","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/EPProgramManager.sol:296","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/EPProgramManager.sol:319"],"claim":"The signed unit-update messages are plain `toEthSignedMessageHash(keccak256(abi.encodePacked(...)))` payloads containing user, units, program id(s), and nonce, but no chain id, verifying contract, or other domain separator.","impact":"A valid Stack signer signature for one manager deployment can be reused on another deployment or chain with the same signer, program id, user, and unused nonce, causing unauthorized unit updates and reward claims outside the intended domain.","paths":["Obtain a valid signature for `user`, `newUnits`, `programId`, and `nonce` on manager A.","Submit the same payload and signature to manager B, or to the same deployment on another chain, where the signer and program id match and the nonce has not been consumed.","The signature check passes because the digest does not bind the authorization to a chain or contract address."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Repeated startFunding leaves residual treasury and subsidy streams","locations":["superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidEPProgramManager.sol:282","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidEPProgramManager.sol:299","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidEPProgramManager.sol:315","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidEPProgramManager.sol:322","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidEPProgramManager.sol:370","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidEPProgramManager.sol:374","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidEPProgramManager.sol:618","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidEPProgramManager.sol:643"],"claim":"`startFunding()` has no guard against an already funded program. Each call overwrites `_fluidProgramDetails[programId]`, but `_updateFundingFlowRateFromTreasury()` and `_updateSubsidyFlowRate()` add the new deltas to the existing global flows. Later `stopFunding()` or `cancelProgram()` subtract only the latest stored rates.","impact":"A repeated start can leave old funding and subsidy flow components running after the program is supposedly stopped or cancelled, continuously draining the treasury into the manager and/or tax distribution pool and causing accounting insolvency or long-lived leakage.","paths":["Owner starts a program with funding and subsidy rates A.","Before stopping it, owner calls `startFunding()` again for the same `programId` with rates B.","The stored details now contain only B, while the treasury and subsidy flows include A+B.","When the program is stopped or cancelled, the manager subtracts only B, leaving A running."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-005","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Pumponomics swap has no slippage bound","locations":["superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidLocker.sol:639","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidLocker.sol:644","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidLocker.sol:650","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidLocker.sol:654","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidLocker.sol:664"],"claim":"`_pump()` executes a Uniswap V3 `exactInputSingle` swap with `amountOutMinimum = 0`. The later liquidity mint slippage check does not bound this swap output because the mint uses the fixed `supAmount` provided by the caller and the remaining WETH balance after the swap.","impact":"MEV searchers can sandwich `provideLiquidity()` transactions and force the 1% pump swap to execute at a manipulated price, extracting value from locker owners and reducing the FLUID received by the locker.","paths":["Attacker observes a `provideLiquidity()` transaction.","Attacker front-runs to move the ETH/FLUID pool price against the locker.","The locker executes `_pump()` with `amountOutMinimum = 0`.","Attacker back-runs to restore the price and captures the spread."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-006","severity":"Low","confidence":"high","title":"Fontaine unlocks can be terminated by any account in the final day","locations":["superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/Fontaine.sol:145","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/Fontaine.sol:147","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/Fontaine.sol:160","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/Fontaine.sol:167","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/Fontaine.sol:175"],"claim":"`terminateUnlock()` has no caller restriction. Once the unlock reaches `endDate - EARLY_END`, any address can stop the recipient, provider, and staker flows and force the remaining balances to be paid or distributed immediately.","impact":"A third party cannot steal the funds because leftovers go to the recipient and pools, but they can force the final-day payout timing and tax distribution snapshot, potentially front-running expected pool unit changes or altering recipient cash-flow timing.","paths":["Observe a Fontaine whose unlock is within one day of `endDate`.","Call `terminateUnlock()` from any address.","The contract stops all streams and distributes/transfers the remaining balances immediately."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-007","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Permissionless EPProgramManager can cache a malicious SuperToken host and GDA","locations":["superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/EPProgramManager.sol:81","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/EPProgramManager.sol:85","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/EPProgramManager.sol:106","superfluid-org/protocol-monorepo/packages/ethereum-contracts/contracts/apps/SuperTokenV1Library.sol:1849","superfluid-org/protocol-monorepo/packages/ethereum-contracts/contracts/apps/SuperTokenV1Library.sol:1853","superfluid-org/protocol-monorepo/packages/ethereum-contracts/contracts/apps/SuperTokenV1Library.sol:1888","superfluid-org/protocol-monorepo/packages/ethereum-contracts/contracts/apps/SuperTokenV1Library.sol:1913"],"claim":"The base `EPProgramManager.createProgram()` is permissionless and accepts any `ISuperToken`. `SuperTokenV1Library` caches host and GDA addresses in single contract-wide storage slots the first time a state-changing GDA helper is used, so a malicious first token can cause the manager to cache attacker-controlled framework addresses.","impact":"If the base manager is deployed for real programs, an attacker can poison its cached framework addresses before legitimate use. Subsequent program creation may call the attacker-controlled GDA, fail permanently, or create fake/misdirected pools for honest tokens.","paths":["Deploy a malicious token whose `getHost()` returns an attacker-controlled host and GDA.","Call permissionless `EPProgramManager.createProgram()` before legitimate programs are created.","The library stores the malicious host/GDA in the manager's global cache slots.","Later program creation calls reuse the poisoned cached addresses instead of deriving them from the legitimate token."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-008","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"Partial unstake disconnects the locker while staker units remain nonzero","locations":["superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidLocker.sol:375","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidLocker.sol:386","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidLocker.sol:389","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/FluidLocker.sol:392","superfluid-finance/fluid/packages/contracts/src/StakingRewardController.sol:140"],"claim":"`unstake()` reduces `_stakedBalance` and updates staker units to the remaining balance, but then unconditionally calls `FLUID.disconnectPool(STAKER_DISTRIBUTION_POOL)`. When a user partially unstakes, the locker can still have nonzero staking units while disconnected from the distribution pool.","impact":"The remaining staked balance may stop receiving real-time staking/tax distributions until the locker owner reconnects, causing reward loss or confusing accounting for users who expected only the unstaked portion to stop earning.","paths":["A locker has X FLUID staked and is connected to the staker distribution pool.","After the cooldown, the owner calls `unstake(Y)` where `0 < Y < X`.","The controller updates units for `X - Y`, but the locker is disconnected from the pool anyway.","The remaining staked balance has units but is not connected for reward streaming."],"round":1,"source_agents":["opencode_1"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Missing reentrancy guard on FluidLocker.withdrawLiquidity()","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The reported function is explicitly protected with `nonReentrant` at `FluidLocker.sol:452`; the signal is factually incorrect."},{"title":"StakingRewardController.distributeTaxAdjustment() requires access control","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The function only distributes the controller's current FLUID balance according to the already configured allocation and gives the caller no direct benefit. The signal describes keeper-style permissionlessness and does not show realistic protocol harm."},{"title":"Missing event emission in FluidLocker.provideLiquidity()","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Missing telemetry is an observability issue, not a protocol-level vulnerability causing loss, theft, insolvency, lockup, manipulation, or permissionless DoS."},{"title":"MacroForwarder.runMacro() is permissionless","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The upstream forwarder is intentionally permissionless; macros are built with `msg.sender`, and Superfluid authorization still gates operations. The report does not identify a concrete path to move funds or alter flows without the affected account's permissions."},{"title":"SupVestingFactory rounding causes cliffAmount to exceed total amount","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The remainder logic preserves the total schedule: updated cliff plus streamed `flowRate * duration` equals the original amount. The claimed over-allocation is not supported by the arithmetic."},{"title":"FluidEPProgramManager inconsistent program admin assignment","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The owner selecting a nonzero `programAdmin` during creation is an intended permission model, and no exploit path or protocol-level harm was identified."},{"title":"FluidEPProgramManager flow-rate division precision loss","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Integer truncation can leave small amounts undistributed or require conservative allowances, but the signal does not show loss to users or exploitable extraction; it is normal fixed-rate streaming dust."},{"title":"FluidLocker.unlock() missing recipient contract compatibility check","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The code checks `recipient != address(0)`, and Fontaine initialization rejects SuperApps. The report's ERC777 hook concern is not supported by the shown SuperToken transfer/flow usage."},{"title":"SupVesting infinite approval to vesting scheduler","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The scheduler is an immutable constructor dependency, and the attack requires the trusted scheduler or its governance to become malicious. That is an external trust-assumption failure, not a bug in this code path."},{"title":"StakingRewardController tax allocation not initialized","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"This is a deployment/configuration concern. Without a concrete attacker-controlled transition, default allocation behavior is not a reportable protocol vulnerability."},{"title":"Factory ETH withdrawal can fail permanently due to transfer stipend","source_agents":["codex_1"],"reason":"`withdrawETH()` can fail for a governor contract with an expensive receiver, but the same governor can call `setGovernor()` to rotate withdrawals to a compatible address. The candidate does not establish permanent lockup or realistic protocol-level harm."},{"title":"Fontaine.terminateUnlock() lets the caller steal remaining tokens","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The theft impact is incorrect: after termination, provider and staker compensation is distributed to their pools and leftover FLUID is transferred to the configured recipient, not to the caller. The supported portion was merged only as a low-severity timing/snapshot issue."}]}
